Veteran Yoruba singer, Salawa Abeni dazzled her audience at the musical concert during the Ake Arts and Book Festival on Wednesday. The event, which took place at the June 12 Cultural centre in Abeokuta, Ogun State had the wife of the Kaduna State Governor, Yasmin El-Rufai in attendance, among other guests. Other performers at the concert included Celeste, Joyce,Adunni Nefretiti, Aramide, Salawa Abeni and several others. Ake Festival's 2017 theme is 'This f-word' and has more women artists and writers this year. The festival is an annual event which features creatives from across the globe.